internalContents.title: * [Joining a Team] Find Your Work Items (2974)
internalContents.description:
mark covello created:
Summary [Joining a Team] Find Your Work Items
Description Find your work items

When you accepted the invitation to join the team, work items like this one were created for the tasks you need to perform to complete joining the team.

At any time, if you wish to find the work items that are assigned to you, you can use the My Work or Team Central views.

There are also a number of default queries created for you. To browse these queries:

1. Open the Team Artifacts View and expand the node corresponding to the connected project area of the team you just joined.

2. Expand the Work Items node.

3. Expand the Shared Queries node.

4. Expand the Predefined node.

5. Double click on the Open assigned to me query.

The Work Items view will open and display your assigned work items.

For additional details on using Jazz Work Items, consult the Getting Started with Work Items help topic.

See any terms you don't recognize? You may also wish to consult the Glossary for the Rational solution for Collaborative Lifecycle Management.

internalContents.title: * [Joining a Team] Create a Repository Workspace (2973)
internalContents.description:
mark covello created:
Summary [Joining a Team] Create a Repository Workspace
Description Create a Repository Workspace

To create a new repository workspace to work with your new Jazz team:

1. In the Team Artifacts view, right-click the node corresponding to your connected project area and select Open.

2. Switch to the Links tab of the opened Project Area editor.

3. In the Artifacts section, expand the Source Control node.

4. Right click on the stream and select New -> Repository Workspace....

5. Specify the repository workspace name. Click Next.

6. Click Finish.

You now have a repository workspace loaded with all the components of the team's stream.

For additional details on using Jazz Source Control, consult the
Getting Started with Jazz Source Control help topic.

See any terms you don't recognize? You may also wish to consult the Glossary for the Rational solution for Collaborative Lifecycle Management.
